TY  - JOUR
AU  - Yung, Chris
T1  - Venture Capital and the Market for Talent during Booms and Busts
PY  - 2017
Y1  - 2017/08/01
DO  - 10.1093/rof/rfw038
JO  - Review of Finance
JA  - Rev Financ
VL  - 21
IS  - 5
SP  - 1875
EP  - 1899
SN  - 1572-3097
AB  - I develop and test a model in which the characteristics of entrepreneurs and VCs are jointly determined by real investment opportunities. By inducing the entry of inept agents, booms inflate the dispersion in ability on both sides of the market. Consistent with these predictions, venture fund return data show that 1) new entrants in hot markets are associated with high cross-sectional dispersion in abnormal returns, and 2) the worst performing funds in the sample are disproportionately likely to be new entrants in hot markets.
Y2  - 3/26/2024
UR  - https://doi.org/10.1093/rof/rfw038
ER  - 



